saveShortcut

public static boolean saveShortcut(User aUser,
                                   BusinessArea aBA,
                                   java.lang.String aSysPrefix,
                                   java.lang.String aName,
                                   java.lang.String aQuery,
                                   java.lang.String aDesc,
                                   java.lang.String aFilter,
                                   int aView,
                                   boolean aIsDefault,
                                   boolean aIsPublic,
                                   boolean aIsListAll,
                                   boolean aIsBAShortcut)
This method creates a shortcut object and stores it in the specified user's webconfig.

Parameters:
aUser - user to whom the shortcut belongs to.
aSysPrefix - business area prefix the shortcut belongs to.
aName - Name of the shortcut.
aQuery - Query definition of the shortcut.
aDesc - Text part if any present in the shortcut.
aFilter - Filter value when the shortcut was saved.
aView - View of the search page when the shortcut is saved.
aIsDefault - Default property of the shortcut.
aIsPublic - Public property of the shortcut.
aIsListAll - ListAll property of the shortcut.
Returns:
True if the shortcut is successfully deleted. False otherwise.
